@35701=~You can now gain a metamagic ability. These abilities empower the next spell you cast, but cause it to use up a higher-level spell slot. Choose one to see its description:~

@36001=~Widen Spell~
@36002=~Widen Spell
(Metamagic)

Spell Level Increase: +1

Widen Spell increases the area of effect of the character's next spell by 50%. For example, a fireball will have a 22-foot radius rather than a 15-foot radius. Widen Spell does nothing to spells that do not have an area of effect.~
@36003=~Maximize Spell~
@36004=~Maximize Spell
(Metamagic)

Spell Level Increase: +3

Maximize Spell causes the character's next spell to deal maximum damage or restore the maximum number of hit points.~
@36005=~Extend Spell~
@36006=~Extend Spell
(Metamagic)

Spell Level Increase: +1

Extend Spell doubles the duration of the character's next spell. Extend Spell cannot extend spell effects with a base duration of less than 5 rounds.~
@36007=~Safe Spell~
@36008=~Safe Spell
(Metamagic)

Spell Level Increase: +1

Safe Spell lets the character shape the area of their next spell to avoid harming allies. Their next spell will only harm enemies if it is an area of effect spell.~
@36009=~Intensify Spell~
@36010=~Intensify Spell
(Metamagic)

Spell Level Increase: +1 to +8

Intensify Spell makes the character's next spell harder to resist. The character can choose how many spell levels to increase the spell by; for each level increase, any saving throw against the spell is made at an additional -1 penalty.~
@36011=~Empower Spell~
@36012=~Empower Spell
(Metamagic)

Spell Level Increase: +2

Empower Spell increases most numerical characteristics of the character's next spell by 50%. Characteristics that can be increased this way include damage, healing, and stat bonuses.~
@36013=~Quicken Spell~
@36014=~Quicken Spell
(Metamagic)

Spell Level Increase: +2

Quicken Spell lets the character cast their next spell instantly. Not only does the quickened spell have no casting time, it can be cast even if the character has already cast another spell in the same round. However, no more than one spell can be quickened per round.~
@36015=~Persistent Spell~
@36016=~Persistent Spell
(Metamagic)

Spell Level Increase: +4

Persistent Spell sets the duration of the character's next spell to one day. This stacks with Extend Spell, which will extend the duration to two days if both are used. Persistent Spell cannot extend spell effects with a base duration of less than 5 rounds.~
@36017=~Mass Spell~
@36018=~Mass Spell
(Metamagic)

Spell Level Increase: +5

Mass Spell lets the character cast their next spell in an area of effect. The spell will affect all creatures within 15 feet of the target. Mass Spell works with spells that are normally single-target, even if they normally only affect the caster, like Mirror Image. However, since Mass Spell replaces the spell's original area of effect, it will not work well with spells that already had an area of effect.~
@36019=~Irresistible Spell~
@36020=~Irresistible Spell
(Metamagic)

Spell Level Increase: +5

Irresisitible Spell makes the character's next spell offer no Saving Throw. Irresistible Spell can only be used with spell effects that weaken or damage the target; it does not work with effects that kill or disable the target, including stun, paralysis, hold, charm, confusion, fear, feeblemind, blindness, petrification, polymorph, instant death, or disintegration.~
