Blood Rage is an even more intense form of berserker rage. When cast, the recipient immediately becomes uncontrollably berserk and attacks the nearest creature, even if the recipient was not previously in combat. While under Blood Rage, the target's Hit Points are unknown, and <PRO_HESHE> is immune to paralysis, pain, and harmful mind-affecting spells (charm, fear, hold, stun, sleep, confusion, feeblemind). In addition, the target's movement rate is doubled and <PRO_HESHE> gains +5 to hit, +7 to damage, and a -5 Armor Class penalty. A non-allied creature is allowed a Save vs. Spell at -3 to resist the spell.~
